'''Oumar Diakité''' (born 20 December 2003) is an Ivorian-French<ref>{{Cite web |last=Demba |first=Varore |date=24 April 2024 |title=Reims-Oumar Diakité : «Depuis tout petit, j'ai baigné dans la culture ivoirienne» - Football |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/news-football/montpellier-modibo-sagnan-depuis-tout-petit-jai-baigne-dans-la-culture-malienne/ |access-date=7 August 2025 |website=Sport News Africa |language=fr-FR}}</ref> [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]], on loan from {{French football updater|Reims}} club [[Stade de Reims|Reims]], and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Liefering|Liefering]]|url=https://www.fc-liefering.at/de/fc-liefering/team/bullenherde/diakite/|title=Oumar Diakite}}</ref>

==Club career==
Diakité joined [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] from [[ASEC Mimosas]] on 12 January 2022 and was quickly sent on loan to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]'s farm team, [[FC Liefering|Liefering]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|url=https://www.kicker.de/salzburg-lotst-mit-oumar-diakite-das-naechste-talent-in-die-mozartstadt-885747/artikel|title=Salzburg lotst mit Oumar Diakite das nächste Talent in die Mozartstadt|date=12 January 2022|access-date=14 January 2023|language=german}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=spox.com|url=https://www.spox.com/at/sport/fussball/oesterreich/2201/Artikel/red-bull-salzburg-holt-talent-oumar-diakite.html|title=Red Bull Salzburg holt Talent Oumar Diakite|date=12 January 2022|accessdate=14 January 2023|language=german|archive-date=5 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205105901/https://www.spox.com/at/sport/fussball/oesterreich/2201/Artikel/red-bull-salzburg-holt-talent-oumar-diakite.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut in a league match against [[SKN St. Pölten]] in 20 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/02/20/austria/1-liga/skn-sankt-polten/usk-anif/3525106/|title=SKN St. Pölten vs. Liefering |date=20 February 2022}}</ref> Diakité scored his first goal against [[SK Rapid Wien II]] in the league match on 3 April.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=laola1.at|url=https://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/2--liga/spielbericht/2021-22/2--liga-im-live-stream--rapid-ii---fc-liefering/|title=Rapid II gleicht in Nachspielzeit ein 0:2 aus|date=3 April 2022|language=German}}</ref>

On 21 June 2023, Diakité signed up for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade de Reims]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stade-de-reims.com/vitesse-et-percussion-sur-le-front-de-lattaque-stadiste/|trans-title=Speed and percussion on the front of the stadium attack!|title=Vitesse et percussion sur le front de l'attaque stadiste!|language=French|website=www.stade-de-reims.com|date=21 June 2023|accessdate=21 June 2023}}</ref>

Diakité scored his first goal for Stade de Reims on 3 September 2023, in a Ligue 1 match against [[FC Metz]]. He was named in the starting lineup, and the match ended in a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite web|date=3 September 2023 |language=fr |title=Football - À Metz, Oumar Diakité a enfin été récompensé avec le Stade de Reims |url=https://www.lunion.fr/id516966/article/2023-09-03/football-metz-oumar-diakite-enfin-ete-recompense-avec-le-stade-de-reims |website=www.lunion.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On 10 March 2024, Diakité scored the equalising goal against [[Paris Saint-Germain]], bringing the score to 2–2. He was later voted Reims Player of the Match by the club's supporters.

On 5 September 2025, Diakité joined [[Belgian Pro League]] side [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]] on loan for one year, with an option for a permanent transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Africafoot |first=L'équipe |date=2025-09-01 |title=Oumar Diakité finalement prêté au Cercle Bruges |url=https://africafoot.com/oumar-diakite-finalement-prete-au-cercle-bruges/ |access-date=2025-09-05 |website=AfricaFoot |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Oumar Diakité versterkt de groen-zwarte aanval {{!}} Cercle Brugge KSV |url=https://cerclebrugge.be/en/news/articles/oumardiakite |access-date=2025-09-05 |website=cerclebrugge.be |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Diakité was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]] for a set of [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] matches in June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=fifciv.com|url=https://www.fifciv.com/?q=elim-can-2023-civ-zam-du-3-juin-2022-des-renforts-chez-les-el%C3%A9phants/|title=Elim. CAN 2023 (CIV-ZAM Du 3 Juin 2022) : Des Renforts Chez Les Eléphants|date=31 May 2022|language=French}}</ref> He was removed from the squad on 6 June 2022, with a minor injury in training.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=fifciv.com|url=https://www.fifciv.com/?q=el%C3%A9phants-bless%C3%A9-diakit%C3%A9-oumar-quitte-la-s%C3%A9lection/|title=Eléphants : Blessé, Diakité Oumar Quitte La Sélection|date=6 June 2022|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=africatopsports.com|url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2022/06/06/cote-divoire-victime-dune-fracture-diakite-oumar-quitte-la-selection/|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE : VICTIME D'UNE FRACTURE, DIAKITÉ OUMAR QUITTE LA SÉLECTION|date=6 June 2022|language=French}}</ref> He debuted in a 1–0 win over [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] on 9 September 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|title=La Côte d'Ivoire bat le Lesotho sur le score de 1 but à 0 au stade Laurent Pokou de San Pedro. Le but ivoirien a été inscrit par Ibrahim Sangaré à la 16e minute|website=rti.info|language=fr|date=9 September 2023|access-date=9 September 2023|archive-date=4 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231004142837/https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in the 27-man squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] hosted in Ivory Coast.<ref>{{cite web |date=28 December 2023 |title=LA LISTE |url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl |access-date=16 January 2024 |publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]] |language=pt |via=[[Facebook]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=5 January 2024 |title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE |url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf |publisher=Confederation of African Football}}</ref> During the quarter-final match against [[Mali national football team|Mali]], he scored the winning goal in the stoppage time of extra time, securing a 2–1 victory and qualification to the semi-finals, which he would miss due to receiving a second yellow card following his celebration.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/africa-cup-of-nations/2024/mali-v-ivory-coast-afcon-quarter-final-live_sto10004333/story.shtml |title=Ivory Coast 2-1 Mail AET: Oumar Diakite scores last minute winner as hosts book Africa Cup of Nations semi-final place |publisher=Eurosport |date=3 February 2024 }}</ref>

Diakité was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Diakité was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

